  "prompt": "What hotel in Ladakh would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "When it comes to finding a hotel in Ladakh that is safe for unmarried couples, it largely depends on the attitude and policies of the particular establishment. Here are a few recommendations based on travelers' experiences:\n\n1. **The Grand Dragon Ladakh**: Known for its quality service and hospitality, this hotel is more likely to be accepting and offer privacy to unmarried couples.\n\n2. **Hotel Ladakh Residency**: This hotel is reputed for its friendly environment and comfortable accommodations, making it a good choice for couples.\n\n3. **Zaltak Eco Resort**: A serene and beautiful resort setting that emphasizes privacy and comfort for all its guests, including unmarried couples.\n\n4. **Hotel Omasila**: A well-known hotel in Leh that offers a decent level of service and privacy, suitable for couples looking to avoid any undue harassment.\n\n5. **The Zen Ladakh**: With modern amenities and a welcoming atmosphere, this hotel aims to provide a safe and respectful stay for all guests.\n\nIt's important to note that most hotels in tourist areas such as Ladakh tend to be more accepting of unmarried couples. When booking a room, you might want to directly inquire about their policies to ensure a hassle-free stay. Additionally, carrying valid IDs and ensuring both partners are consenting adults can help avoid any issues.",
